//- Form radio mixin
//- Renders a configurable radio input with label.
//- Designed for use in groups where multiple radio buttons share the same `name`
//- but have different `value`s. Supports default checked state.
//-
//- Parameters:
//-   id       - **String** — Unique identifier for the <input> element.
//-              Also used by the <label> `for` attribute.
//-              Example: 'contact-email', 'contact-phone'.
//-              Default: none (required).
//-   label    - **String** — Visible label text displayed next to the radio button.
//-              Example: 'Email', 'Phone'.
//-              Default: none (required).
//-   name     - **String** — Name attribute used to group radio buttons.
//-              All radios with the same `name` belong to one group.
//-              Example: 'contact', 'gender'.
//-              Default: none (required).
//-   value    - **String** — Value submitted when this radio is selected.
//-              Example: 'email', 'phone', 'male', 'female'.
//-              Default: none (required).
//-   checked  - **Boolean** — Whether this radio is selected by default.
//-              Example: true, false.
//-              Default: false.
//-
//- Behavior:
//-   - Renders a `.form-check` wrapper for spacing and alignment.
//-   - The input always has `.form-check-input` class for styling.
//-   - The label always has `.form-label` class and is linked via `for=id`.
//-   - Radios with the same `name` are mutually exclusive: only one can be selected.
//-   - If `checked=true`, this radio is preselected in its group.
//-
//- Notes about styling and classes:
//-   - Visual appearance is controlled by `.form-check-input` and `.form-label`
//-     styles in your SCSS.
//-   - To add custom classes or attributes, extend the mixin or wrap it.
//-   - Ensure `id` is unique to avoid duplicate `for`/`id` collisions.
//-
//- Examples:
//-   // Basic radio group
//-   .form-group
//-     span.form-label Communication method
//-     +formRadio('contact-email', 'Email', 'contact', 'email')
//-     +formRadio('contact-phone', 'Phone', 'contact', 'phone')
//-
//-   // Radio with default checked
//-   .form-group
//-     span.form-label Gender
//-     +formRadio('gender-male', 'Male', 'gender', 'male', true)
//-     +formRadio('gender-female', 'Female', 'gender', 'female')
//-
//-   // Multiple radios with custom values
//-   .form-group
//-     span.form-label Preferred language
//-     +formRadio('lang-en', 'English', 'language', 'en')
//-     +formRadio('lang-ua', 'Ukrainian', 'language', 'ua')
//-     +formRadio('lang-de', 'German', 'language', 'de')
mixin formRadio(id, label, name, value, checked=false)
  .form-check
    input.form-check-input(
      type='radio',
      id=id,
      name=name,
      value=value,
      checked=checked
    )
    label.form-label(for=id)= label
